WEBVTT

00:07.624 --> 00:09.191
Did you miss me, Gal?

00:09.192 --> 00:12.660
Madalena, I have traveled
1,000 miles to see you.

00:12.662 --> 00:14.396
I fought pirates.

00:14.397 --> 00:16.797
I stared death in the face a dozen times,

00:16.799 --> 00:18.667
and I did all that to be with a woman

00:18.668 --> 00:21.970
who chose a fierce and cruel man
over my unconditional love.

00:21.971 --> 00:24.070
- So...
- You crossed my mind, yes.

00:24.841 --> 00:26.809
Then why didn't you act happy to see me?

00:26.810 --> 00:28.544
To be honest, I don't know how to feel.

00:28.545 --> 00:30.511
Isabella told me
you wanted me to rescue you.

00:30.513 --> 00:31.914
Did you even know I was coming?

00:31.915 --> 00:34.650
Well, I found out earlier today,
and as soon as I did,

00:34.651 --> 00:36.685
I made a plan for us to be together.

00:36.686 --> 00:38.821
Yeah, well, <i>I</i> had a plan, as well.

00:38.822 --> 00:41.490
We were gonna live
in a cottage by the sea.

00:41.491 --> 00:44.193
We were gonna make love, plant a garden...

00:44.194 --> 00:45.294
Have children.

00:45.295 --> 00:47.796
I was gonna sing songs of your beauty.

00:47.797 --> 00:49.364
Oh, Gal.

00:49.365 --> 00:50.599
That sounds awful.

00:51.501 --> 00:53.135
Look around.

00:53.136 --> 00:54.937
I live in a castle.

00:54.938 --> 00:56.905
And you know
what I've learned about myself?

00:56.906 --> 00:59.708
I really like stuff.

00:59.709 --> 01:02.110
I mean, why would I give all this up

01:02.111 --> 01:04.413
to get fat and pregnant
and grow my own food?

01:04.414 --> 01:06.348
So, you didn't want me to come?

01:08.718 --> 01:11.887
I should never have trusted Isabella.

01:11.888 --> 01:14.022
How could someone so small
tell such a big lie?

01:14.023 --> 01:15.524
Well, none of that matters now.

01:15.525 --> 01:17.993
I have a plan that will allow me
to remain as queen,

01:17.994 --> 01:21.963
and you will be
well taken care of as my...

01:21.964 --> 01:23.098
Special companion.

01:23.099 --> 01:24.933
Your boy toy, you mean.

01:24.934 --> 01:27.436
Is that how you see me? Hmm?

01:27.437 --> 01:29.671
As some well-groomed, ruggedly handsome,

01:29.672 --> 01:31.706
yet oddly delicate-featured plaything?

01:32.942 --> 01:34.009
Yeah.

01:35.044 --> 01:37.546
Madalena, I've got something to say,

01:37.547 --> 01:40.782
and I've come a really,
<i>really</i> long way to say it.

01:40.783 --> 01:42.117
Oh, no.

01:42.118 --> 01:44.219
♪ I want you, I need you ♪

01:44.220 --> 01:45.820
♪ You cut me, and I bleed you ♪

01:45.821 --> 01:47.956
♪ You're like some kind of sonnet ♪

01:47.957 --> 01:49.758
♪ All I want to do is read you ♪

01:49.759 --> 01:51.526
- ♪ And I love you ♪
- I know.

01:51.527 --> 01:53.561
- ♪ I mean I love you ♪
- Yes. Thanks.

01:53.562 --> 01:55.430
- ♪ I said I love you ♪
- You did.

01:55.431 --> 01:59.668
♪ And now don't you want
to tell me something, too? ♪

02:02.605 --> 02:04.239
♪ I love you ♪

02:04.240 --> 02:07.509
♪ As much as someone like me
can love anyone ♪

02:07.510 --> 02:07.946
Huh?

02:07.948 --> 02:11.112
♪ I mean, I love
how we make people stare ♪

02:11.113 --> 02:13.047
♪ We're quite the stunning pair ♪

02:13.049 --> 02:14.891
♪ In other words, you love me ♪

02:14.893 --> 02:18.386
♪ As much as someone like me
can love anyone ♪

02:18.387 --> 02:18.992
Okay.

02:18.994 --> 02:21.856
♪ I mean, I love how when we hit the hay ♪

02:21.857 --> 02:23.358
♪ It's more than just okay ♪

02:23.359 --> 02:24.000
Right?

02:24.002 --> 02:27.295
♪ I'd absolutely say
more like middling to fair ♪

02:27.296 --> 02:28.730
Yeah. Wait. What?

02:28.731 --> 02:30.932
♪ Dance with me ♪

02:30.933 --> 02:34.235
♪ Can't you see
how freaking gorgeous we look? ♪

02:34.236 --> 02:37.505
♪ Can't you feel
the frantic beat of our hearts ♪

02:37.506 --> 02:41.576
♪ As our various parts rub
with such delicious friction? ♪

02:41.577 --> 02:43.144
♪ So, that's all you really... ♪

02:43.145 --> 02:45.213
♪ Dance with me ♪

02:45.214 --> 02:48.916
♪ Why not finish what's already begun? ♪

02:48.917 --> 02:51.018
♪ So, what you're saying is you love me ♪

02:51.019 --> 02:53.154
- ♪ I love you ♪
- ♪ Really love me ♪

02:53.155 --> 02:55.590
- ♪ I love you ♪
- ♪ And always loved me? ♪

02:55.591 --> 02:58.893
♪ As much as someone like me
can love anyone ♪

03:02.698 --> 03:05.032
Does that clear things up for you?

03:05.033 --> 03:06.334
No.

03:06.335 --> 03:08.035
And when did you learn how to dance?

03:08.036 --> 03:10.872
Galavant - 01x06
Dungeons and Dragon Lady

03:11.345 --> 03:13.218
Are you hearing this, Gareth?

03:13.220 --> 03:17.425
My own wife tries to trick me
into killing my favorite chef

03:17.425 --> 03:19.292
so she can save her ex-boyfriend.

03:19.293 --> 03:20.260
You sure it was her?

03:20.261 --> 03:21.428
Pretty girl, tiny waist, big eyes?

03:21.429 --> 03:22.562
Definitely, My King.

03:23.731 --> 03:25.699
No one has it as bad as I do, Gareth.

03:25.700 --> 03:27.634
- No one!
- Aaaaaaaah!

03:29.370 --> 03:31.104
Uh... Don't worry.

03:31.105 --> 03:34.240
Why do I continually allow
people to treat me this way?

03:34.241 --> 03:35.041
Oh, come on.

03:35.042 --> 03:37.477
Forget I'm your king
and talk to me like your friend.

03:37.478 --> 03:38.511
All right.

03:38.512 --> 03:40.013
You keep acting like a prat.

03:40.014 --> 03:41.448
You need to be more of a geezer.

03:41.449 --> 03:44.684
You know, I've tried to tell you
time and time again.

03:44.685 --> 03:46.920
You don't turn your ear.

03:48.089 --> 03:49.155
Oh, Gareth.

03:49.156 --> 03:50.690
I can't understand a word you say.

03:50.691 --> 03:52.826
Let me ask you this, then.

03:52.827 --> 03:54.727
Do you like me, Gareth?

03:54.728 --> 03:58.731
- I mean, you know, as a... as a person?
- Aaaaaaah!

04:01.368 --> 04:02.535
I got to go.

04:02.536 --> 04:03.670
My queen needs me.

04:03.671 --> 04:05.471
- <i>Your</i> queen?
- Mm.

04:05.472 --> 04:08.141
Are you hearing this? Now it's <i> his</i> queen.

04:08.142 --> 04:09.876
Fine. Go ahead.

04:09.877 --> 04:11.644
Leave me, too. Be that guy.

04:11.645 --> 04:12.512
Go. Go.

04:12.513 --> 04:13.746
Yeah, okay.

04:16.016 --> 04:17.784
Why am I like this?

04:17.785 --> 04:20.623
Why do I continually allow
people to treat me this way?

04:20.625 --> 04:22.024
- Sire!
- Hmm?

04:22.027 --> 04:24.457
I-I think I know something
that may help you.

04:24.458 --> 04:26.025
Really? What?

04:26.026 --> 04:28.027
Have you ever heard of Xanax?

04:28.028 --> 04:29.162
Xanax?

04:29.163 --> 04:31.764
Is he that new magician
I'm hearing so much about?

04:31.765 --> 04:32.899
Merlin's replacement?

04:32.900 --> 04:33.966
Yes, My King.

04:33.967 --> 04:36.669
I-I occasionally buy herbs from him.

04:36.670 --> 04:39.305
Herbs? For what? F-f-for cooking?

04:40.307 --> 04:41.507
Yeah... f-for cooking.

04:42.676 --> 04:45.578
All right, it's worth a shot.
Let's go see Xanax.

04:45.579 --> 04:47.647
I should probably put on
something more casual.

04:47.648 --> 04:49.048
The brown.

04:53.887 --> 04:55.555
Uh, hi.

04:55.556 --> 04:57.523
Um, why are we back in the dungeon?

04:57.524 --> 05:00.026
Just wait here. I'll come
get you when it's time.

05:00.027 --> 05:02.161
Someone's coming to help execute my plan.

05:02.162 --> 05:03.329
Move along.

05:05.265 --> 05:06.999
Galavant! Galavant!

05:09.436 --> 05:11.270
I thought you were dead.

05:11.271 --> 05:13.206
You mean because you betrayed me,
you thought they would hang me?

05:13.207 --> 05:14.273
Because you <i> betrayed</i> me?

05:14.274 --> 05:15.441
Oh, trust me, sir,

05:15.442 --> 05:17.910
I have been guilting
the crap out of her down here.

05:17.911 --> 05:19.979
King Richard said if I didn't
deliver the jewel <i> and</i> you,

05:19.980 --> 05:21.347
he would kill my parents.

05:21.348 --> 05:22.982
I tried to warn you...

05:22.983 --> 05:25.151
so many songs, so many asides.

05:25.152 --> 05:26.919
The point is, Queen Madalena,

05:26.920 --> 05:28.688
you have the jewel and you have Galavant.

05:28.689 --> 05:30.790
- You must release my parents.
- Must I?

05:30.791 --> 05:32.325
- Yes. You have to.
- Have I?

05:32.326 --> 05:33.559
- Yes.
- Really?

05:33.560 --> 05:34.860
Why are you just repeating
everything I say as a question?

05:34.861 --> 05:36.662
Am I just repeating everything
you say as a question?

05:36.663 --> 05:38.097
You... Don't hear it?

05:38.098 --> 05:39.432
-<i>I</i> hear it. Yeah. 
- Yeah.

05:39.433 --> 05:42.968
- You're sort of doing it a little bit.
- I had a deal with King Richard.

05:42.969 --> 05:44.937
My dear girl...

05:44.938 --> 05:46.739
I am not King Richard.

05:46.740 --> 05:51.243
But I will enjoy killing the girl
who tried to eat my leftover man mutton.

05:55.949 --> 05:58.984
Is... Anyone else uncomfortable?

06:01.121 --> 06:02.421
Gareth.

06:02.422 --> 06:04.127
Cut her face.

06:04.129 --> 06:05.396
Torture the rest.

06:05.398 --> 06:07.800
- Gala...
- Excuse me?

06:07.802 --> 06:11.026
I said torture them. Is there a problem?

06:11.231 --> 06:12.632
No. There's not a problem.

06:12.633 --> 06:14.567
I <i> like</i> torturing. I'm pretty good at it.

06:14.568 --> 06:16.102
I once kept a guy alive for a week,

06:16.103 --> 06:18.270
and he was just a head and a finger.

06:18.271 --> 06:20.139
But that order came from the king,

06:20.140 --> 06:21.240
and I serve My King.

06:21.241 --> 06:24.176
Your king is weak, Gareth. You know this.

06:24.177 --> 06:26.879
He cries like a baby,
he cares like a woman.

06:26.880 --> 06:29.081
He makes decoupage footstools as a hobby.

06:29.082 --> 06:30.483
Hey! That was a birthday present.

06:30.484 --> 06:32.084
He got me that so I could have a sit down.

06:32.085 --> 06:34.420
You're a dog, Gareth.

06:34.421 --> 06:36.789
And a dog needs a strong master.

06:38.024 --> 06:39.758
Now sic 'em.

06:44.331 --> 06:46.165
Here we are, sir.

06:46.166 --> 06:47.500
Are we safe?

06:47.501 --> 06:49.869
This neighborhood looks a little dodgy.

06:49.870 --> 06:51.170
Don't worry, sire, we'll be fine.

06:51.171 --> 06:53.305
Just... Try not to look scared.

06:54.574 --> 06:56.842
Hello. Nice to see you.

