07:05.318 --> 07:06.852
What do you want?

07:08.822 --> 07:10.656
Uh, we're here to see Xanax.

07:10.657 --> 07:12.224
He's in the attic.

07:12.225 --> 07:13.992
Mom! It's a laboratory!

07:13.993 --> 07:15.260
Call it a laboratory.

07:15.261 --> 07:16.395
It's an attic.

07:22.469 --> 07:25.938
Hmm. This is... Cozy.

07:25.939 --> 07:29.441
King Richard, may I present
Xanax The Magician.

07:30.710 --> 07:32.678
Actually, I'm not legally allowed

07:32.679 --> 07:34.680
to call myself a magician anymore

07:34.681 --> 07:37.015
'cause of the whole...  Thing.

07:37.016 --> 07:38.450
Don't worry.

07:38.451 --> 07:40.886
Think of me as a spiritual guide.

07:40.887 --> 07:42.754
I'm allowed to... Call myself that.

07:42.755 --> 07:44.223
<i>Anyone</i> can. It's meaningless.

07:46.459 --> 07:48.460
Look at his shiny little hat, toad.

07:48.461 --> 07:50.262
Ribbit.

07:50.263 --> 07:51.563
Who's that person?

07:51.564 --> 07:53.265
It's toad. He's cool.

07:53.266 --> 07:54.199
Ribbit.

07:54.200 --> 07:56.068
Don't ask.

07:57.036 --> 07:58.603
He <i> was</i> a toad.

07:58.604 --> 08:00.172
I did a spell...

08:00.173 --> 08:03.809
turned him into a human-ish... Type thing.

08:03.810 --> 08:05.243
So, uh, yeah. I flipped it.

08:06.279 --> 08:07.846
That's very good.

08:07.847 --> 08:09.448
Anyway, what can I do for you gents?

08:09.449 --> 08:11.550
Well, it's... No big deal, really.

08:11.551 --> 08:13.452
We were just... in the neighborhood,

08:13.453 --> 08:15.320
and, um, I was sort of wondering,

08:15.321 --> 08:17.289
you know, why I am the way I am,

08:17.290 --> 08:19.925
and he mentioned
you might be able to help me.

08:19.926 --> 08:22.093
Xanax can help <i> anything.</i>

08:22.094 --> 08:23.094
Wonderful.

08:25.064 --> 08:26.731
Bit of wind there.

08:26.732 --> 08:28.033
Ooh.

08:28.034 --> 08:29.901
Right. Let's get you started.

08:29.902 --> 08:32.437
This is a... Kind of disgusting
little workstation, isn't it?

08:32.438 --> 08:35.106
You see the toilet?
It's basically a window.

08:35.107 --> 08:39.144
And by "window,"
I mean "hole"... in the wall.

08:39.145 --> 08:40.412
It works.

08:40.413 --> 08:41.546
One of them.

08:41.547 --> 08:43.280
Oh. Toad spotted it.
You'd love that, wouldn't you?

08:44.984 --> 08:46.217
That goes in.

08:46.218 --> 08:48.320
Ready. Let's do this.

08:49.655 --> 08:50.989
Oooooooooooh.

08:52.525 --> 08:54.793
Now the magic words.

08:56.328 --> 08:59.130
Abracadabra.

08:59.131 --> 09:01.433
Alakazam.

09:01.434 --> 09:07.372
Habrazamdabra, flanimal ham.

09:07.373 --> 09:08.473
Oooooh.

09:08.474 --> 09:10.809
Try that now. It's all magic.

09:10.810 --> 09:13.711
- So, I just... Drink that down, eh?
- Yeah.

09:13.712 --> 09:16.180
- Straight down the gullet?
- Yeah.

09:16.181 --> 09:19.317
- Ooh. That is pungent.
- Yeah. That's the anus.

09:19.318 --> 09:21.719
Oh, what the hell.

09:21.720 --> 09:22.787
Oh, God.

09:22.788 --> 09:23.788
Mm.

09:23.789 --> 09:25.056
Hmm.

09:25.057 --> 09:28.426
Takes a little while to kick in
with a strong-willed...

09:28.427 --> 09:29.460
- I'm feeling it.
- Yeah.

09:31.030 --> 09:32.997
Oh, wow.

09:38.915 --> 09:42.351
All right, boss, we need an escape plan.

09:42.352 --> 09:44.720
- What are you thinking?
- Here's what I think.

09:46.323 --> 09:49.191
If you really break it down...

09:49.192 --> 09:51.827
"I love you as much as someone
like me could love anyone"

09:51.828 --> 09:53.028
can mean a lot of things.

09:53.029 --> 09:55.029
Oh, come on, man.

09:55.031 --> 09:56.665
Oh, just let it go!

09:56.666 --> 09:58.066
She's the worst!

09:58.067 --> 10:00.335
- She imprisoned us.
- She stole our jewels.

10:00.335 --> 10:02.670
- Yeah, not a fan.
- You want to know what I think?

10:02.672 --> 10:03.972
I think you're in a dungeon

10:03.973 --> 10:06.174
wondering if the woman
that put you there loves you.

10:06.175 --> 10:09.344
And the real question is,
why do you still love her?

10:09.345 --> 10:11.046
I mean, yes, she's beautiful,

10:11.047 --> 10:13.081
in a perfect-skin, perfect-body,
perfect-hair kind of way,

10:13.082 --> 10:14.449
if you're into that sort of thing.

10:14.450 --> 10:15.751
Mm.

10:15.752 --> 10:17.653
I know you, Galavant.

10:17.654 --> 10:20.222
I know your heart, and you deserve better.

10:20.223 --> 10:23.191
You deserve to be with someone
who will lift you up as a man,

10:23.192 --> 10:25.727
someone who will fight <i> with</i> you,
not against you.

10:25.728 --> 10:27.763
Maybe someone who's small and cute

10:27.764 --> 10:29.631
and ethnically hard to pin down.

10:32.502 --> 10:33.769
What you're saying is...

10:37.540 --> 10:39.074
you <i> don't</i> think she loves me?

10:39.075 --> 10:41.176
Bloody hell.

10:41.177 --> 10:43.545
Oh, please, just stop the torture
and kill me already.

10:43.546 --> 10:44.629
I haven't started yet.

10:44.631 --> 10:45.528
He's not part of it?

10:45.530 --> 10:48.051
Will everybody just shut up?!

10:48.151 --> 10:51.186
- Do you want to know what real torture is?
- No, I'm good. Thanks.

10:55.625 --> 10:58.660
Imagine being loyal
to someone your whole life.

10:58.661 --> 10:59.895
I'm not gonna tell you who,

10:59.896 --> 11:02.864
but hypothetically,
we'll call him "the king."

11:04.567 --> 11:07.002
He's a bit of a ponce, but I like him.

11:07.003 --> 11:10.138
Then he gets married
to this rump-fed basket cockle,

11:10.139 --> 11:13.074
who, hypothetically,
we'll call "the queen."

11:13.075 --> 11:14.776
We all know who you're
talking about, Gareth.

11:14.777 --> 11:17.345
But let me be cryptic
for a minute, will ya?!

11:17.346 --> 11:19.481
Just give me that!

11:19.482 --> 11:22.717
Now, she's not like "the king."

11:22.718 --> 11:25.420
But she's strong, and I mire strength.

11:25.421 --> 11:28.990
But, then again, I've sworn
an oath to protect the king.

11:28.991 --> 11:30.325
So I don't know what to do.

11:30.326 --> 11:33.161
I mean, that's real torture,
isn't it, lads?

11:43.105 --> 11:45.240
Welcome to Richard's journey

11:45.241 --> 11:48.376
to find out why he is the way he is.

11:48.377 --> 11:50.979
There's bottles of water in easy reach.

11:50.980 --> 11:52.881
Please stay hydrated.

11:52.882 --> 11:54.149
And no kissing.

11:54.150 --> 11:55.783
Of course. Wait. What?

11:55.784 --> 11:57.485
Oh... Shouldn't be an issue.

11:57.486 --> 11:59.387
But it <i> has</i> happened in the past,

11:59.388 --> 12:01.823
so I made a blanket rule... no kissing.

12:02.925 --> 12:05.226
Mm. Good idea.

12:05.227 --> 12:07.629
Okay. Everyone ready?

12:07.630 --> 12:08.730
Ribbit.

12:08.731 --> 12:12.700
♪ Close your eyes, open your mind ♪

12:12.701 --> 12:16.704
♪ Your journey's about to begin ♪

12:16.705 --> 12:20.508
♪ Relax your karma and try not to barf ♪

12:20.509 --> 12:25.013
♪ As the universe starts to spin ♪

12:25.014 --> 12:28.683
♪ Hocus-pocus, expealadocious ♪

12:28.684 --> 12:32.520
♪ Set your aura free ♪

12:32.521 --> 12:37.458
♪ Petrificus totalis,
drink deeply from the chalice ♪

12:37.459 --> 12:48.269
♪ Tell us what you see-e-e-e-e-e ♪

12:53.909 --> 12:55.042
I see a door!

12:57.779 --> 12:58.913
Oi! What did I say?

12:58.914 --> 13:00.381
No...

13:00.382 --> 13:02.116
Go through it.

13:02.117 --> 13:03.884
It's opening on its own!

13:03.885 --> 13:05.820
That's magic.

13:12.160 --> 13:14.228
This is the day my father died.

13:14.229 --> 13:17.531
♪ The king is dead, long live the king ♪

13:17.532 --> 13:21.035
♪ The king is dead, long live the king ♪

13:21.036 --> 13:24.638
♪ Where is his son,
who'll inherit everything? ♪

13:24.639 --> 13:27.041
Is that you, sire? So handsome.

13:27.043 --> 13:29.811
No. It's my much older brother, Kingsley.

13:29.811 --> 13:32.213
- I can't see anything!
<i>- That's</i> me.

13:32.214 --> 13:34.415
♪ Shut up, you ♪

13:34.416 --> 13:35.783
I can't see anything!

13:35.784 --> 13:37.218
♪ Shut up ♪

13:37.219 --> 13:38.185
Oh, dear.

13:38.186 --> 13:39.720
I ate my feelings.

13:39.721 --> 13:41.322
And a lot of bread.

13:41.323 --> 13:43.123
♪ The sword, Your Highness ♪

13:43.124 --> 13:45.125
♪ Here's the royal sword ♪

13:46.361 --> 13:47.795
No one <i> gives</i> me anything.

13:47.796 --> 13:51.498
♪ To be the king,
you must receive the sword ♪

13:51.499 --> 13:54.301
If I want something, I <i> take</i> it.

13:54.302 --> 13:55.936
And I don't want to be any king.

13:56.972 --> 13:59.239
Oh, but, Kingsley, it's your destiny.

13:59.240 --> 14:01.742
We literally named you "Kingsley."

14:01.743 --> 14:02.876
God told us to.

14:02.877 --> 14:04.845
It's not like we were being trendy.

14:04.846 --> 14:07.181
My destiny lies
beyond the castle walls, mother.

14:07.182 --> 14:09.216
I'm going to conquer and kill

14:09.217 --> 14:11.719
and spread bastard children
throughout the land,

14:11.720 --> 14:13.654
like wildflower seeds.

14:13.655 --> 14:15.823
Somebody else
can sit on their ass and rule.

14:15.824 --> 14:17.791
♪ But who? ♪

14:17.792 --> 14:19.560
- ♪ Who? ♪
- ♪ But who? ♪

14:19.561 --> 14:21.829
♪ Who? ♪
♪ But who? ♪
♪ But who? ♪

14:26.501 --> 14:27.601
Dickie?

14:27.602 --> 14:28.702
"Dickie."

14:29.737 --> 14:31.572
Brilliant.

14:31.573 --> 14:32.739
Gareth.

14:32.740 --> 14:34.041
Aye.

14:34.042 --> 14:35.609
You shall be the king's guard.

14:35.610 --> 14:38.312
I'm only 10, but... All right.

14:38.313 --> 14:40.847
I'm Gareth, and I'll faithfully
serve you, My King.

14:40.848 --> 14:44.051
♪ The sword, your highness ♪

14:44.052 --> 14:48.288
♪ Here's your royal sword ♪

14:48.289 --> 14:50.257
♪ To be the king, you mu... ♪

14:50.258 --> 14:52.626
Actually, I think I <i> will</i> take the sword.

14:54.028 --> 14:56.196
Good luck... Dickie.

14:59.767 --> 15:01.234
How humiliating.

15:01.235 --> 15:02.469
That's it.

15:02.470 --> 15:04.304
It <i> was</i> humiliating.

15:04.305 --> 15:07.307
Everything comes back to this moment.

15:07.308 --> 15:09.009
I have spent my entire life

15:09.010 --> 15:11.511
behaving as if
I'm everyone's second choice...

15:11.512 --> 15:13.713
my parents', my kingdom's,
and now my queen's.

15:13.721 --> 15:16.290
Let's go take back my kingdom!

15:18.386 --> 15:19.986
Where's that bloody door?

15:21.022 --> 15:23.156
Well, how the hell
are we supposed to get up there?

15:23.157 --> 15:25.492
That was amazing!

15:25.493 --> 15:26.893
Thank you, Xanax.

15:26.894 --> 15:28.962
I now know exactly what I must do.

15:28.963 --> 15:30.797
Come on, chef! To the horses!

15:30.798 --> 15:32.532
I wouldn't ride just yet.

15:32.533 --> 15:34.334
Again, it's a legal thing.

15:34.335 --> 15:38.304
A guy once... he took his horse
through a farmers market,

15:38.305 --> 15:39.873
and there was... "raaaaaah!"

15:39.874 --> 15:42.275
The hooves and the crushing
and s-screaming, so...

15:42.276 --> 15:44.377
- Ugh...
- Let the potion wear off.

15:44.378 --> 15:46.246
An hour, say?

15:46.247 --> 15:47.280
Oh. Okay.

15:47.281 --> 15:50.416
Hey, in that case, you guys want to
see my room from when I was a kid?

15:50.417 --> 15:51.818
Wow.

15:51.819 --> 15:53.253
Let's... let's do this.

15:53.254 --> 15:53.953
Great.

16:03.196 --> 16:04.529
Listen, Galavant...

16:04.530 --> 16:06.965
I know what I did to you was horrible...

16:06.966 --> 16:08.667
probably even worse
than what Madalena did to you,

16:08.668 --> 16:10.669
because at least she had
the guts to do it to your face.

16:10.670 --> 16:12.471
And I won't say it again,

16:12.472 --> 16:14.473
but I'm more sorry than you'll ever know.

16:14.474 --> 16:17.209
Just so you know... I'm really sorry.

16:17.210 --> 16:19.411
Oh, God. You must feel
really bad. You're babbling.

16:20.513 --> 16:22.514
You only babble when you feel really bad.

16:22.515 --> 16:24.950
I do not babble when I feel bad.

16:24.951 --> 16:26.084
I'm not saying it's a bad thing.

16:26.085 --> 16:28.220
To be honest,
I've rather grown to like it.

16:28.221 --> 16:30.222
But you <i> do</i> babble, princess.

16:30.223 --> 16:32.491
Princess Isa-babble.

16:32.492 --> 16:35.026
"Princess Isa-babble."

16:35.027 --> 16:36.503
Okay, hang on a sec.

16:36.529 --> 16:38.764
Babbling is when someone talks nonsense,

16:38.765 --> 16:40.399
and I do not talk nonsense.

16:40.400 --> 16:43.869
I mean... Sometimes, at times,
I guess I do babble,

16:43.870 --> 16:46.071
but it's only because I have
a lot going on in my head and...

16:46.072 --> 16:47.406
oh. Never mind.

16:47.407 --> 16:49.541
Look, you don't have to feel bad.

16:49.542 --> 16:51.443
They're your parents.

16:51.444 --> 16:53.578
When you care about somebody...

16:53.579 --> 16:55.213
You'll do anything for them.

16:56.382 --> 16:59.751
Love is... Strange.

16:59.752 --> 17:01.953
And sometimes kind of gross.

17:01.954 --> 17:05.123
♪ It's embarrassingly gassy ♪

17:05.124 --> 17:09.327
♪ And it leaves its dirty underwear ♪

17:09.328 --> 17:12.564
♪ In piles around the place ♪

17:12.565 --> 17:15.666
♪ Love is rude, it has a sort of smell ♪

17:15.667 --> 17:19.404
♪ And it thinks that you don't notice ♪

17:19.405 --> 17:20.972
♪ And it blurts out things ♪

17:20.973 --> 17:25.676
♪ That make you want
to smack its stupid face ♪

17:25.678 --> 17:28.647
♪ And it's awkward and confusing ♪

17:28.648 --> 17:31.916
♪ It annoys you half to death ♪

17:31.917 --> 17:33.752
♪ Then it grins that dopey grin ♪

17:33.753 --> 17:37.856
♪ And you can't catch your breath ♪

17:37.857 --> 17:41.359
♪ Love is strange
and sometimes sort of smug ♪

17:41.360 --> 17:44.963
♪ And it's really, really bossy ♪

17:44.964 --> 17:47.632
♪ And it messes with your head ♪

17:47.633 --> 17:51.870
♪ Till you're a hopeless basket case ♪

17:51.871 --> 17:53.204
♪ And it's stubborn ♪

17:53.205 --> 17:54.205
♪ It's insulting ♪

17:54.206 --> 17:56.074
♪ It's obnoxious ♪

17:56.075 --> 17:57.575
♪ It's the worst ♪

17:57.576 --> 18:03.615
♪ You keep pushing it away,
and you fall in headfirst ♪

18:03.616 --> 18:07.385
♪ Love is strange ♪

18:07.386 --> 18:09.554
♪ And often pretty drunk ♪

18:09.555 --> 18:12.323
♪ It looks different without makeup ♪

18:12.324 --> 18:16.060
♪ And it's nothing like the fairy tales ♪

18:16.061 --> 18:19.197
♪ You grow up dreaming of ♪

18:19.198 --> 18:20.298
♪ Love is weird ♪

18:20.299 --> 18:22.300
♪ Love is dumb ♪

18:22.301 --> 18:25.236
♪ Love is strange ♪

18:25.237 --> 18:36.714
♪ And that's what makes it lo-o-o-o-o-ve ♪

18:36.715 --> 18:38.883
I've been so blind.

18:38.884 --> 18:40.985
Madalena never loved me.

18:40.986 --> 18:43.087
When you love someone,
you shout it from the rooftop,

18:43.088 --> 18:44.555
not couch it in a riddle.

18:44.556 --> 18:45.823
Or in a song.

18:45.824 --> 18:47.225
That's more cinematic.

18:48.660 --> 18:50.395
Well, how's that for timing?

18:50.396 --> 18:52.196
Our stars are finally aligning

18:52.197 --> 18:54.165
on the same day I'm going to die.

18:54.166 --> 18:55.900
No.

18:57.436 --> 19:00.505
No, you're <i> not</i> gonna die today.

19:00.506 --> 19:02.340
And <i> you're</i> not gonna die today.

19:02.341 --> 19:04.909
And <i> you're</i> not gonna die today.

19:06.445 --> 19:07.778
You might already be dead.

19:08.981 --> 19:11.282
Well, what are you going to do?

19:11.283 --> 19:12.483
What else?

19:12.484 --> 19:14.385
Save the day.

19:17.589 --> 19:19.490
Have these been open the whole time?

19:20.926 --> 19:23.060
No one thought to check?

19:23.061 --> 19:24.495
Really?

19:30.802 --> 19:32.636
Is it done? Did you torture them?

19:32.637 --> 19:34.305
Nah.

19:34.306 --> 19:35.740
But I gave you an order.

19:35.741 --> 19:38.109
I don't give a rat's ass
about your orders.

19:38.110 --> 19:40.878
I might be a dog, but at least
I'm a loyal one, love.

19:42.147 --> 19:45.149
Now, I serve the king,
so I only follow <i> his</i> orders.

19:45.150 --> 19:48.819
That is so nice to hear.

19:48.820 --> 19:52.423
You have always been
my most loyal friend, Gareth.

19:52.424 --> 19:55.159
I know you're not a hugger,
but if you were,

19:55.160 --> 19:57.194
I would wrap myself around you

19:57.195 --> 19:59.463
like a leather jacket made of love.

19:59.464 --> 20:00.898
Mm.

20:00.899 --> 20:01.899
Xanax?

20:01.900 --> 20:03.267
- So much Xanax.
- Mm.

20:03.268 --> 20:04.435
Okay, couple of things.

20:04.436 --> 20:07.771
First, chef, I am so munchy.

20:07.772 --> 20:09.673
Could you make me, like, a cheesy omelette

20:09.674 --> 20:12.109
with some ham chunks,
potatoes fried in bacon grease?

20:12.110 --> 20:13.544
- Right away, sire.
- Excellent.

20:13.545 --> 20:15.746
Next, I'm breaking up with you.

20:15.747 --> 20:19.149
Gareth, would you please escort
Madalena down to the dungeon

20:19.150 --> 20:20.784
and lock her up forever?

20:20.785 --> 20:21.752
Huh?

20:23.955 --> 20:24.955
Come on.

20:24.956 --> 20:26.590
Wait!

20:26.591 --> 20:28.959
It would be rude to imprison your queen

20:28.960 --> 20:31.195
when we have such a special visitor.

20:31.196 --> 20:32.596
What visitor?

20:32.597 --> 20:34.832
What are you talking about?

20:35.934 --> 20:37.401
Hello, brother.

20:40.371 --> 20:41.371
Kingsley?

20:41.372 --> 20:42.439
What's he doing here?

20:42.440 --> 20:43.707
What are you doing here?

20:43.708 --> 20:45.042
I'm here to take your life.

20:45.043 --> 20:46.833
My life?

20:46.835 --> 20:48.667
Your lifestyle.

20:49.314 --> 20:50.647
Your kingdom.

20:50.648 --> 20:54.184
Of course, if you get in my way,

20:54.185 --> 20:58.200
I'll have to take your life, too...

21:01.018 --> 21:03.018
Dickie.

21:04.060 --> 21:06.023
This is gonna to be fun.

